        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 8:02PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>..Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Lake and
northeastern Klamath Counties through 845 PM PDT...

At 801 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms near
Head Of The River Campground, or 41 miles east of Crater Lake,
moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Head Of The River Campground, Silver Creek Marsh Campground,
Crescent, Jackson Creek Forest Camp, Antler Campground And Trailhead,
Thompson Reservoir Campground, and Gilchrist.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
